          "title": "Complement Addition & Subtraction",
          "explainer": "## Complement Addition & Subtraction\n\n### The Core Idea\nInstead of subtracting directly, **add the complement** to make the math easier.\n\n### Complements to 10\n- Complement of 3 → 7 (3 + 7 = 10)\n- Complement of 8 → 2\n- Complement of 6 → 4\n\n### Subtract from Powers of 10\nTo compute **1000 − 637**:\n1. Complement each digit to 9 (except last to 10)\n2. 6→3, 3→6, 7→3\n3. Answer: **363**\n\n### Speed Rule\nFor subtraction from 10^n: complement each digit to 9, last digit to 10.\n\n### TMSCA Tip\nThis lets you subtract from round numbers in under 2 seconds.",
