          "explainer": "## Modular Arithmetic\n\n### What is Mod?\na mod n = remainder when a is divided by n.\n\n### Key Rules\n1. (a + b) mod n = ((a mod n) + (b mod n)) mod n\n2. (a × b) mod n = ((a mod n) × (b mod n)) mod n\n\n### Last Digit Problems\nLast digit = number mod 10\n- 7^100: Pattern 7,9,3,1 repeats every 4. 100 mod 4 = 0 → last digit **1**\n- 3^2024: Pattern 3,9,7,1. 2024 mod 4 = 0 → last digit **1**\n\n### Divisibility Rules\n- **By 3:** sum of digits ÷ 3\n- **By 4:** last 2 digits ÷ 4\n- **By 7:** double last digit, subtract from rest\n- **By 8:** last 3 digits ÷ 8\n- **By 11:** alternating sum ÷ 11",
