          "explainer": "## The Pigeonhole Principle\n\n### Statement\nIf n+1 pigeons go into n holes, at least one hole has ≥ 2 pigeons.\n\n### Generalized\nN objects into k boxes → at least one box has ≥ ⌈N/k⌉ objects.\n\n### Classic Problems\n**Problem 1:** Among 13 people, at least 2 share a birth month.\n13 people, 12 months → collision guaranteed.\n\n**Problem 2:** Among any 5 integers, some pair has an even sum.\nRemainders mod 2: {0,1}. 5 numbers, 2 boxes → ≥3 in one → pair with same parity → even sum.\n\n**Problem 3:** Pick 5 points in a 2×2 square. Two are within √2 distance.\nDivide into 4 unit squares → some square has 2 points → max distance in unit square = √2.",
