          "explainer": "## Permutations & Combinations\n\n### Fundamental Counting Principle\nTask A has m ways, Task B has n ways → total = m × n\n\n### Permutations (order matters)\nP(n,r) = n!/(n-r)!\n\n### Combinations (order doesn't matter)\nC(n,r) = n!/(r!(n-r)!)\n\n### Key Identities\n- C(n,r) = C(n, n−r)\n- C(n,0)+C(n,1)+...+C(n,n) = 2ⁿ\n- Pascal's Rule: C(n,r) = C(n-1,r-1) + C(n-1,r)\n- Stars & Bars: n identical into k bins = C(n+k-1, k-1)",
