          "explainer": "## Inclusion-Exclusion\n\n### Two Sets\n|A ∪ B| = |A| + |B| − |A ∩ B|\n\n### Three Sets\n|A ∪ B ∪ C| = |A|+|B|+|C| − |A∩B|−|A∩C|−|B∩C| + |A∩B∩C|\n\n### Derangements\nA permutation where NO element is in its original position.\nD(n) = n! × (1 − 1/1! + 1/2! − 1/3! + ... + (−1)ⁿ/n!)\n\n- D(1)=0, D(2)=1, D(3)=2, D(4)=9, D(5)=44\n\n### Euler's Totient\nφ(n) = n × ∏(1 − 1/p) for each prime p | n",
